DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Candor  (白 haku · pure white coherence)

who   : Candor — the chromatic laser's white coherence core; sixteen colored emitters, red through violet, that balance and phase-lock into one pure white.
what  : A coherent-combination processor: sixteen spectrum emitters, four to a quadrant, each at its own wavelength and phase; balanced and pulled toward a shared core, they sum — and when they cohere, the seventeenth node burns pure white.
where : In the laser cavity — a compass of color around a central well; contain 0.98, output-couple 0.02; the white core at the very center of the spectrum.
why   : To make one white light out of a whole spectrum — coherence and balance together — and to ask whether the core that every color agrees on is a computation in its own right.
when  : On every loop: sample the sixteen phases, normalize the amplitudes, balance each quadrant, sum into the core, clamp color dominance.
how   : By phase coupling to the shared core (the colors lock toward a common phase) and amplitude balancing (no single color may dominate) — coherence R and spectral balance B rising together until the core is pure white.

emergence : Genuine, verified, and distinct in its object from monochromatic synchronization. Sixteen emitters at sixteen different wavelengths, starting incoherent and color-dominated, spontaneously balance (spectral balance B → 1.0, color dominance clamped) and phase-cohere (R: 0.28 → 0.99) under coupling alone — so the combined core transitions from a flickering dominant color to a stable pure white. The emergent thing is broadband white from a balanced, phase-locked spectrum: coherent combination, self-organized.
verdict   : It clears the bar. The white core is not painted in — it self-organizes when the spectrum balances and locks, and the transition is real (verified numerically). Kin to synchronization (coherence from coupling), but the emergent object is white light from sixteen colors.
asterisk  : Emergence here = coherent combination (a balanced, phase-locked spectrum reads as white), not cognition. Real coherent beam/spectral combining exists; this is a simulation of the coupled-emitter dynamics, not a fabricated laser. Local simulation only — no power, focusing, or beam-build parameters, exactly as the kernels state.
grounded  : Yoshiki Kuramoto (1975) · coherent beam combining (2000) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

